# Refrigerator Temperature & Humidity Monitoring System

## Overview

This project is an ESP32-based dual-zone temperature and humidity monitoring system designed for refrigeration applications. The system uses two independent I2C buses to communicate with two SHT40 temperature and humidity sensors, allowing simultaneous monitoring of multiple compartments such as refrigerator and freezer sections.

The project continuously measures environmental conditions and outputs real-time sensor readings through the serial monitor for debugging, testing, and data analysis purposes.

---

## Features

* Dual independent I2C buses
* Simultaneous monitoring of two SHT40 sensors
* Real-time temperature measurement
* Real-time humidity measurement
* Automatic I2C device scanning during startup
* Detailed serial debugging output
* Sensor initialization verification
* Error detection and reporting
* Configurable debug levels
* High precision sensor measurements
* ESP32-based architecture
* PlatformIO compatible

---

## Hardware Requirements

### Microcontroller

* ESP32 Development Board

### Sensors

* 2 × SHT40 Temperature & Humidity Sensors

### Connections

#### Sensor 1 (I2C Bus 1)

| ESP32 Pin | SHT40 |
| --------- | ----- |
| GPIO21    | SDA   |
| GPIO22    | SCL   |
| 3.3V      | VCC   |
| GND       | GND   |

#### Sensor 2 (I2C Bus 2)

| ESP32 Pin | SHT40 |
| --------- | ----- |
| GPIO32    | SDA   |
| GPIO33    | SCL   |
| 3.3V      | VCC   |
| GND       | GND   |

---

## Software Requirements

* PlatformIO
* Visual Studio Code
* ESP32 Arduino Framework

### Required Libraries

```ini
Adafruit SHT4x Library
Adafruit BusIO
Wire
```

---

## Startup Sequence

During startup the firmware performs the following operations:

1. Initializes serial communication.
2. Scans I2C Bus 1 for connected devices.
3. Scans I2C Bus 2 for connected devices.
4. Detects and initializes Sensor 1.
5. Detects and initializes Sensor 2.
6. Configures both sensors for High Precision mode.
7. Begins continuous environmental monitoring.

---

## Example Serial Output

```text
👋 System Initialization Successful!

🔍 I2C Scan on Wire1 (GPIO21=SDA, GPIO22=SCL)
✅ I2CBUS_1 Device found at 0x44

🔍 I2C Scan on Wire2 (GPIO32=SDA, GPIO33=SCL)
✅ I2CBUS_2 Device found at 0x44

✅ SHT40_1 initialized
✅ SHT40_2 initialized

T_1: 4.25 °C | RH_1: 82.1 %
T_2: -17.80 °C | RH_2: 61.4 %
```

---

## Debug Levels

The firmware supports multiple debug levels:

```cpp
#define __DEBUG_LEVEL_SILENT__      0
#define __DEBUG_LEVEL_ERROR__       1
#define __DEBUG_LEVEL_ESSENTIAL__   2
#define __DEBUG_LEVEL_VERBOSE__     3
```

Current configuration:

```cpp
#define __DEBUG_LEVEL__ __DEBUG_LEVEL_VERBOSE__
```

This setting enables detailed startup diagnostics and live sensor readings.

